^*Bhondo717:^*N OK, just a quick review of NT overcalls over a weak 2.  You should overcall 2N over a weak 2 with a normal strong NT and a stopper in the bid suit. It is a bit risky, particularly when you only have 15. But the upside is that it is very descriptive. So if you have a bad 15, you might make a takeout double, but with a good 15-18 balanced, overcalling 2N is best.  You cannot pass with that many points, because you are letting the opponents steal you blind if you do. When the opponents preempt, unfortunately it makes it more difficult for you, and you have to take some calculated risks.|
